cant events.\n__NOTOC__\n* [[#19th century in film|19th century in film]]\n* 20th century in film:\n** [[#1900s|1900s]] \u2013 [[#1910s|1910s]] \u2013 [[#1920s|1920s]] \u2013 [[#1930s|1930s]] \u2013 [[#1940s|1940s]] \u2013 [[#1950s|1950s]] \u2013 [[#1960s|1960s]] \u2013 [[#1970s|1970s]] \u2013 [[#1980s|1980s]] \u2013 [[#1990s|1990s]]\n* 21st century in film:\n** [[#2000s|2000s]] \u2013 [[#2010s|2010s]] \u2013 [[#2020s|2020s]]\n\n==19th century in film==\n{{See also|19th century in film}}\n* '''[[1888 in film|1888]]''' \u2013 Thelost and earliest surviving film, the ''[[Roundhay Garden Scene]]'' shot in [[Leeds]], [[West Yorkshire]], [[England]], through a groundbreaking 20 [[film frame|frames]] per second.\n* '''[[1893 in film|1893]]''' \u2013 [[Thomas Edison]] creates \"America's First Film Studio\", [[Edison's Black Maria|Black Maria]]; The first film shown publicly on the [[Kinetoscope]], a system given to Edison, is ''[[Blacksmith Scene|Blacksmiths]]''.\n* '''[[1895 in film|1895]]''' \u2013 In France, [[Auguste and Louis Lumi\u00e8re|the Lumi\u00e8re brothers]] screen ten films at the Salon Indien du Grand Caf\u00e9 in Paris; [[Gaumont Film Company]], the oldest ever film studio, is founded by inventor [[L\u00e9on Gaumont]].\n* '''[[1896 in film|1896]]''' \u2013 [[Path\u00e9-Fr\u00e8res]] is founded. The Lumi\u00e8re brothers release six more short films, one of which is ''[[L'Arriv\u00e9e d'un train en gare de La Ciotat]]''.\n* '''[[1897 in film|1897]]''' \u2013 [[Vitagraph]] is founded in [[New York City]]\n* '''[[1899 in film|1899]]''' \u2013 [[Georges M\u00e9li\u00e8s]] releases ''[[The Dreyfus Affair (film series)|The Dreyfus Affair]]'' and ''[[Cendrillon (1899 film)|Cendrillon]]'' (first screen adaptation of the traditional fairy tale ''[[Cinderella]]''); earliest known use of a colour motion picture film footage by  [[Edward Raymond Turner]]<ref>{{cite news|title=World's first colour film footage viewed for first time|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-19557914|publisher=BBC News England|accessdate=14 September 2012|date=12 September 2012}}</ref>.\n\n==1900s==\n{{See also|1900s in film}}\n* '''[[1900 in film|1900]]''' \u2013 ''[[Sherlock Holmes Baffled]]'', ''[[Joan of Arc (1900 film)|Joan of Arc]]'', ''[[The Enchanted Drawing]]''\n* '''[[1901 in film|1901]]''' \u2013 ''[[Star Theatre (film)|Star Theatre]]'', ''[[Stop Thief!]]'', ''[[Scrooge, or, Marley's Ghost]]''\n* '''[[1902 in film|1902]]''' \u2013 ''[[A Trip to the Moon]]''\n* '''[[1903 in film|1903]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Great Train Robbery (1903 film)|The Great Train Robbery]]''\n* '''[[1904 in film|1904]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Impossible Voyage]]''; [[Titanus]] is founded \n* '''[[1905 in film|1905]]''' \u2013 ''[[Adventures of Sherlock Holmes; or, Held for Ransom]]''\n* '''[[1906 in film|1906]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Story of the Kelly Gang]]'', ''[[Dream of a Rarebit Fiend (1906 film)|Dream of a Rarebit Fiend]]'', ''[[Humorous Phases of Funny Faces]]''; [[Nordisk Film]] is founded \n* '''[[1907 in film|1907]]''' \u2013 ''[[Ben-Hur (1907 film)|Ben-Hur]]'', ''[[L'Enfant prodigue (film)|L'Enfant prodigue]]''\n* '''[[1908 in film|1908]]''' \u2013 ''[[Fantasmagorie (1908 film)|Fantasmagorie]]'', ''[[A Visit to the Seaside]]'', ''[[The Taming of the Shrew (1908 film)|The Taming of the Shrew]]'', ''[[The Thieving Hand]]'', ''[[The Assassination of the Duke of Guise]]''; first use of [[Kinemacolor]]; [[Path\u00e9 News]] invents the [[newsreel]].\n* '''[[1909 in film|1909]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Country Doctor (1909 film)|The Country Doctor]]'', ''[[A Corner in Wheat]]'', ''[[Princess Nicotine; or, The Smoke Fairy]]'', ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (1909 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''; [[35 mm movie film|35 mm film]] becomes a filmmaking standard across the world.\n\n==1910s==\n{{See also|1910s in film}}\n* '''[[1910 in film|1910]]''' \u2013 ''[[In Old California (1910 film)|In Old California]]'', ''[[In the Border States]]'', ''[[White Fawn's Devotion]]''\n* '''[[1911 in film|1911]]''' \u2013 ''[[L'Inferno (film)|L'Inferno]]'', ''[[Baron Munchausen's Dream]]'', ''[[Defence of Sevastopol]]'', ''[[The Lonedale Operator]]''\n* '''[[1912 in film|1912]]''' \u2013 ''[[Independen\u0163a Rom\u00e2niei]]'', ''[[The Musketeers of Pig Alley]]''; [[Universal Pictures]] and [[Paramount Pictures]], Hollywood's two oldest major film studios, are founded; [[British Board of Film Classification|British Board of Film Classification (BBFC)]] is established \n* '''[[1913 in film|1913]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Bangville Police]]'', ''[[Fant\u00f4mas (1913 serial)|Fant\u00f4mas]]'', ''[[Barney Oldfield's Race for a Life]]'', ''[[Raja Harishchandra]]''; invention of the [[Trailer (promotion)|film trailer]]\n* '''[[1914 in film|1914]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Perils of Pauline (1914 serial)|The Perils of Pauline]]'', ''[[Tillie's Punctured Romance (1914 film)|Tillie's Punctured Romance]]'', ''[[Judith of Bethulia]]''\n* '''[[1915 in film|1915]]''' \u2013 ''[[The Birth of a Nation]]'', ''[[The Tramp (film)|The Tramp]]'', ''[[Les Vampires]]'', ''[[A Fool There Was (1915 film)|A Fool There Was]]''; [[Fox Film]] is founded\n* '''[[1916 in film|1916]]''' \u2013 ''[[Intolerance (film)|Intolerance]]'', ''[[20,000 Leagues Under the Sea (1916 film)|20,000 Leagues Under the Sea]]'', ''[[Gertie the Dinosaur]]'', ''[[The Queen of Spades (1916 film)|The Queen of Spades]]''; invention of [[Technicolor]]\n* '''[[1917 in film|1917]]''' \u2013 ''[[Rebecca of Sunnybrook Farm (1917 film)|Rebecca of Sunnybrook Farm]]'', ''[[A Man There Was]]''\n* '''[[1918 in film|1918]]''' \u2013 ''[[Stella Maris (1918 film)|Stella Maris]]'', ''[[Mickey (1918 film)|Mickey]]'', ''[[Shifting Sands (film)|Shifting Sands]]''\n* '''[[1919 in film|1919]]''' \u2013 ''[[Blind Husbands]]'', ''[[Broken Blossoms]]'', ''[[True Heart Susie]]'', ''[[Dalagang Bukid]]'', ''[[Male and Female]]''; [[United Artists]] is founded\n\n==1920s==\n{{See also|1920s in film}}\n* '''[[1920 in film|1920]]''' \u2013 ''[[Way Down East]]'', ''